{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Labs Voxel Mesh"], "type": "title", "extent": [0, 20], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [155, 224], "text": [" Convert a Polygon Mesh into a Volume and back into Polygons "]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [224, 360], "text": ["A very common node chain is ", {"text": ["VDB From Polygons"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vdbfrompolygons", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/vdbfrompolygons"}, ", followed immediately by a  ", {"text": ["Convert VDB"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/convertvdb", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/convertvdb"}]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [360, 557], "text": ["This converts your mesh into a Volume and then back to a Mesh. Doing so has the following benefits: It can close small holes in the mesh, give you new even topology and remove interior geometry. "]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [557, 671], "text": ["VoxelMesh is often used to sanitize photogrammetry data, as it will often fix small imperfections on the mesh. "]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [678, 898], "text": ["UVs are generally destroyed while going through the VDB roundtrip. If you would like to transfer UVs from the original mesh back onto the Voxelized, take a look at the ", {"text": ["UV Transfer Node"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/labs--uv_transfer", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/labs--uv_transfer"}]}], "indent": 0, "text": [" "], "role": "item", "extent": [671, 678], "container": true, "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [926, 1051], "text": ["This sets the number of voxels to be generated on the longest axis of the mesh. Note that this is scale independent."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Resolution"], "role": "item", "extent": [910, 926], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1093, 1213], "text": ["This allows you to expand (dilate) or contract (erode) the geometry along the surface normal of the VDB volume."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Dilate/Erode"], "role": "item", "extent": [1075, 1093], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1239, 1368], "text": ["The number of smoothing operations to be applied to the VDB before meshing. This can help remove high frequency details."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Smoothing Iterations"], "role": "item", "extent": [1213, 1239], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 4, "level": 2, "text": ["VDB Smoothing"], "extent": [1051, 1075], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1402, 1640], "text": ["Controls how even the topology of the resulting mesh is. High Adaptivity values mean concentration around areas of high curvature, low curvature means even distribution of polygons\n        ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/voxelmesh_adaptivity.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/voxelmesh_adaptivity.png"}]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Adaptivity"], "role": "item", "extent": [1386, 1402], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1673, 1786], "text": ["This will attempt to transfer any attributes found on the input geometry onto the VDB remeshed geometry."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Transfer Surface Attributes"], "role": "item", "extent": [1640, 1673], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1808, 2031], "text": ["Geometry tends to soften when being voxelized, because some features might sit in between voxels. This strengthens the features and is helpful on hard surfaces.\n        ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/voxelmesh_sharpenfeatures.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/voxelmesh_sharpenfeatures.png"}]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Sharpen Features"], "role": "item", "extent": [1786, 1808], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2051, 2129], "text": ["Tolerance for what edges to consider for the Sharpen Features toggle."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Edge Tolerance"], "role": "item", "extent": [2031, 2051], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2154, 2220], "text": ["Optionally Ray the resulting mesh back onto the original "]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Project to Original"], "role": "item", "extent": [2129, 2154], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2248, 2383], "text": ["The Projection step can generate some undesirably overlapping polygons, this step can relax some of those polygons"]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Post Smooth Iterations"], "role": "item", "extent": [2220, 2248], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 4, "level": 2, "text": ["Meshing"], "extent": [1368, 1386], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [898, 910], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}], "summary": [" Convert a Polygon Mesh into a Volume and back into Polygons "], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": "2.0", "tags": "sidefxlabs,  model, gamedev, voxel, photogrammetry", "namespace": "labs", "internal": "labs::voxelmesh", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "icon": "voxel_mesh_alt"}, "title": ["Labs Voxel Mesh"]}